#39;s Roller Boogie Palace 举办的一次性气候行动活动。 （戴夫·贝内特/盖蒂图片社拍摄）" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/eilish_overheated_4.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/eilish_overheated_4-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/eilish_overheated_4-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/eilish_overheated_4-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/eilish_overheated_4-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/eilish_overheated_4-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>昨天（8 月 30 日）， <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/billie-eilish">Billie Eilish</a>在将过热气候行动活动带回伦敦时向一群“了不起”的合作者致敬。看看下面的内容，以及我们对艾利什的母亲玛吉·贝尔德的采访。</p><p>在一天的会谈结束时，艾利什加入了台上的演讲者——一系列活动家、创新者和思想领袖——并说道：“这太神奇了。我真的很自豪我能成为一名助人之手。”</p><p>在活动早些时候，艾利什和她的母亲玛吉·贝尔德一起谈论了她对旧货购物和可持续时尚的热爱。</p><p> 500 名观众和 Eilish YouTube 上的数千名现场观众观看了以气候行动为主题的演讲节目。 </p><figure id="attachment_3491666" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3491666" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3491666" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/eilish_overheated_1.jpg" alt="2023 年 8 月 30 日，Billie Eilish 和小组成员在 Overheated 活动期间在舞台上摆姿势，这是一项由 Support + Feed 和 Billie Eilish 在英国伦敦 Flipper&#39;s Roller Boogie Palace 举办的一次性气候行动活动。 （戴夫·贝内特/盖蒂图片社拍摄）" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/eilish_overheated_1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/eilish_overheated_1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/eilish_overheated_1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/eilish_overheated_1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/eilish_overheated_1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/eilish_overheated_1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3491666" class="wp-caption-text">比莉·艾利什 (Billie Eilish) 和小组成员在过热期间在舞台上摆姿势（摄影：Dave Benett/Getty Images）</figcaption></figure><p> This was the second time Eilish and her collaborators have hosted Overheated in the capital, after the <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/billie-eilish-announces-climate-focused-event-overheated-in-london-3217206">platform debuted during the singer&#39;s run of shows at The O2</a> in June 2022 – a move that saw one of the world&#39;s most popular indoor concert venues <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/londons-o2-arena-to-go-vegan-for-billie-eilish-residency-3243475">go vegan during the artist&#39;s residency</a> .</p><p> Eilish has been a long-term advocate for climate action – supporting campaigns by groups including <a href="https://www.musicdeclares.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Music Declares Emergency</a> and <a href="https://reverb.org/campaign/music-climate-revolution/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Reverb</a> . Earlier this year, Eilish appeared on the cover of <a href="https://www.vogue.com/article/billie-eilish-climate-activism-january-cover-2022-video">Vogue magazine</a> with a collection of climate organisers.</p><p> Flipper&#39;s Roller Boogie Palace in west London was the venue this time. After the talks concluded, fans were invited to roller skate. Elsewhere, plant-based food was served to the crowd and fans could interact with grassroots climate groups who&#39;d be invited to set up information stands. </p><blockquote class="instagram-media" data-instgrm-captioned data-instgrm-permalink="https://www.instagram.com/reel/Cwlc--rIDu3/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" data-instgrm-version="14" style=" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:658px; min-width:326px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2p